com.cubeia.firebase.api.game.activator
Interface TableFactory

public interface TableFactory

This is the access interface published by the platform to game activators in order to enable them to query the current state of the system and manage the tables.

Author:
lars.j.nilsson

Method Detail

createTable

LobbyTable createTable(int seats,
                       CreationParticipant participant)
Create a new table and return its lobby representation. The second argument must be supplied of the activator wishes to set default lobby attributes, modify the state of the tables or define where in the lobby the table should be located.

If the activator is representing a game which is an adaption of GameSupport the game will be instantiated and set as the state of the table. For this reason it is possible for this method to fail when instantiating the game, in which case it returns null.

Parameters:
seats - Number of seats at the table
participant - Creation participant, may be null
Returns:
The lobby representation of the table, or null if failed

createTables

LobbyTable[] createTables(int tables,
                          int seats,
                          CreationParticipant participant)
Create new tables and return their lobby representation. This method is equivalent with createTable(int, CreationParticipant) but creates multiple tables instead of only one.

As a result the given creation participant will be called sequentially, once per new table.

Parameters:
tables - Number of tables to create, must be positive
seats - Number of seats at the table, must be positive
participant - Creation participant, may be null
Returns:
The lobby representation of the tables, never null

destroyTable

boolean destroyTable(int tableid,
                     boolean force)
This method destroys a table in the system. It can be used to remove old tables. If the second argument is false the platform will fail the request if any players are seated at the table.

NB: This method may be slow, please use destroyTable(LobbyTable, boolean) whenever possible.

Parameters:
tableid - Id of the table to remove
force - True if the table should always be destroyed, false to check for seated players
Returns:
True if the table was destroyed, false otherwise

destroyTable

boolean destroyTable(LobbyTable table,
                     boolean force)
This method destroys a table in the system. It can be used to remove old tables. If the second argument is false the platform will fail the request if any players are seated at the table.

Parameters:
table - Table to remove, must not be null
force - True if the table should always be destroyed, false to check for seated players
Returns:
True if the table was destroyed, false otherwise

listTables

LobbyTable[] listTables()
Get a list of all tables. This method is most likely rather slow and should be used sparingly by the activator.

Returns:
An array of lobby tables, never null

listTables

LobbyTable[] listTables(LobbyTableFilter filt)
Get a list of all tables. This method is most likely rather slow and should be used sparingly by the activator.

Parameters:
filt - Filter to use, null for all tables
Returns:
An array of lobby tables, never null

listTables

LobbyTable[] listTables(LobbyPath path)
Get a list of all tables under a specified path. This method is most likely rather slow and should be used sparingly by the activator.

Parameters:
fqn - Coordinate in the lobby tree, e.g. "a/b/c"
Returns:
An array of lobby tables, never null

listTables

LobbyTable[] listTables(LobbyPath path,
                        LobbyTableFilter filt)
Get a list of all tables under a specified path and with a set filter. This method is most likely rather slow and should be used sparingly by the activator.

Parameters:
fqn - Coordinate in the lobby tree, e.g. "a/b/c"
filt - Filter to use, null for all tables
Returns:
An array of lobby tables, never null
